<subSubSection id="37E2657C4F22FFF7F0FAFC48FDF76D3F" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph id="7F4736F74F22FFF7F0FAFC48FDF76D3F" blockId="15.[192,1441,867,1307]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
The taxonomy of species placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F22FFF7F301FC48FC686B9F" authority="Lepeletier" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[779,1021,931,955]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Mesoplia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F22FFF7F301FC48FCEF6B9F" box="[779,890,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Mesoplia</emphasis>
Lepeletier
</taxonomicName>
is in an unsatisfactory state, hampered by inaccurate information on distributions and unresolved problems of synonymy. The usage of names for Antillean species is therefore compromised. 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F22FFF7F343FC08FB186BDF" author="Snelling, R. R. &amp; R. W. Brooks" box="[841,1165,995,1019]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref16076" refString="Snelling, R. R., and R. W. Brooks. 1985. A review of the genera of cleptoparasitic bees of the tribe Ericrocini (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Contributions in Science, Natural History Museum of Los Angeles County 369: 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1985">Snelling and Brooks (1985)</bibRefCitation>
reviewed the genera of cleptoparasitic bees in the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F22FFF7F241FBE8FD4B6C3F" authorityName="Cockerell &amp; Atkins" authorityYear="1902" box="[587,734,1027,1051]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" rank="tribe" tribe="Ericrocidini">Ericrocidini</taxonomicName>
(misspelled as 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F22FFF7F390FBE8FB806C3F" box="[922,1045,1027,1051]" family="Anthophoridae" pageId="15" pageNumber="23" rank="tribe" tribe="Ericrocini">Ericrocini</taxonomicName>
by these authors: refer to 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F22FFF7F552FBE8FF686C1F" author="Engel, M. S." pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref12483" refString="Engel, M. S. 2005. Family-group names for bees (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). American Museum Novitates 3476: 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="2005">Engel 2005</bibRefCitation>
), including the genus 
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F22FFF7F1F4FBC8FDE76C1F" box="[510,626,1059,1083]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F22FFF7F1F4FBC8FDF86C1F" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[510,621,1059,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Mesoplia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesoplia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
however that work did not extend to the species level. 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F22FFF7F4F8FBCFFA356C1F" author="Moure, J. S." box="[1266,1440,1059,1083]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref14749" refString="Moure, J. S. 1960 b. Notas sobre os tipos de abelhas do Brasil descritas por Perty em 1833 (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). Boletim da Universidade do Parana, Zoologia 6: 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="1960">Moure (1960b)</bibRefCitation>
studied the 
<typeStatus id="A04388554F22FFF7F15EFBA8FE2B6C7F" box="[340,446,1091,1115]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F22FFF7F1E9FBAFFDF46C7F" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[483,609,1091,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Crocisa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipes">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F22FFF7F1E9FBAFFDF46C7F" box="[483,609,1091,1115]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">M. rufipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, commenting on issues of synonymy, and established three species groups within the genus. He placed 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F22FFF7F264FB8FFD7C6C5F" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[622,745,1123,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Crocisa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipes">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F22FFF7F264FB8FFD7C6C5F" box="[622,745,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">M. rufipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F22FFF7F329FB8FFA9A6C5F" authority="(Lepeletier and Serville, 1828)" baseAuthorityName="Lepeletier and Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[803,1295,1123,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Mesoplia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azurea">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F22FFF7F329FB8FFC096C5F" box="[803,924,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">M. azurea</emphasis>
(Lepeletier and Serville, 1828)
</taxonomicName>
in the same group. Several authors have treated 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F22FFF7F27CFB6FFD656CBF" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[630,752,1155,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Crocisa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipes">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F22FFF7F27CFB6FFD656CBF" box="[630,752,1155,1179]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">M. rufipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F22FFF7F323FB6FFC356CBF" baseAuthorityName="Lepeletier and Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[809,928,1156,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Mesoplia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azurea">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F22FFF7F323FB6FFC356CBF" box="[809,928,1156,1179]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">M. azurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as synonyms without providing additional comments (i.e.; 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F22FFF7F176FB48FDB76C9F" author="Cresson, E. T." box="[380,546,1187,1211]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 200" refId="ref11770" refString="Cresson, E. T. 1865. On the Hymenoptera of Cuba. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Philadelphia 4: 1 - 200." type="journal article" year="1865">Cresson 1865</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F22FFF7F226FB48FD726C9F" author="Gundlach, J." box="[556,743,1187,1211]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" refId="ref13348" refString="Gundlach, J. 1886. Contribucion a la entomologia cubana. Tomo II. Hymenopteros. Imprenta La Antilla; Havana. 187 p." type="book" year="1886">Gundlach 1886</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F22FFF7F2FBFB48FC546C9F" author="Dalla Torre, C. G. de" box="[753,961,1187,1211]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" refId="ref12034" refString="Dalla Torre, C. G. de. 1896. Catalogus Hymenopterorum Vol. X, Apidae (Anthophilia). Engelmann; Leipzig. 643 p." type="book" year="1896">Dalla Torre 1896</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F22FFF7F3C1FB48FBCE6C9F" author="Friese, H." box="[971,1115,1187,1211]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="196 - 201" refId="ref12921" refString="Friese, H. 1902. Beitrag zur Apidenfauna der grossen Antillen. Zeitschrift fur Systematische Hymenopterologie und Dipterologie 2: 196 - 201." type="journal article" year="1902">Friese 1902</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F22FFF7F46FFB48FB626C9F" author="Ducke, A." box="[1125,1271,1187,1211]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="51 - 116" refId="ref12129" refString="Ducke, A. 1912. Die naturlichen Bienengenera Sudamerikas. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere 34: 51 - 116." type="journal article" year="1912">Ducke 1912</bibRefCitation>
). According to G. Melo (personal communication, 2007), 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F22FFF7F2BFFB2FFCA56CFF" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[693,816,1219,1243]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Crocisa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipes">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F22FFF7F2BFFB2FFCA56CFF" box="[693,816,1219,1243]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">M. rufipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the continental mainland; a revision of the species is in preparation and will clarify the proper names and distributions of the Antillean species, not clarified in 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F22FFF7F17DFAEFFDCA6D3F" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; D. Urban &amp; G. A. R. Melo" box="[375,607,1283,1307]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" refId="ref14912" refString="Moure, J. S., D. Urban, and G. A. R. Melo. 2007. Catalogue of bees (Hymenoptera: Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia; Curitiba. 1058 p." type="book" year="2007">Moure et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
